HEADWORD: Chapbook
<hw>Chap"book`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Chap</er>
to cheapen.]</ety> <def>Any small book carried about for sale by chapmen
or hawkers. Hence, any small book; a toy book.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

